<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="24" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">immediate</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Aboard
                                        the</hi> H.M.S. “<hi rend="smallcaps">Duke of
                                    York</hi>”</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-18">December 18, 1941</date>.]<note n="1" xml:id="d24fn1">The message was transmitted by the British
                                    Embassy to the White House with the notation: “Following message
                                    has been received from H.M.S. <hi rend="italic">Duke of
                                        York</hi>, 18. 21. 41.” Copies were promptly sent to members
                                    of the Joint Board for their consideration; see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_50">p.
                                    50</ref>.</note>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>It is hoped to reach agreement to following main points during
                                conference. <list>
                                    <label>(i)</label>
                                    <item>Fundamental basis of joint strategy.</item>
                                    <label>(ii)</label>
                                    <item>Interpretation of (i) into terms of immediate Military
                                        measures, including re-distribution of forces.</item>
                                    <label>(iii)</label>
                                    <item>Allocation of joint forces to harmonise with (i).</item>
                                    <label>(iv)</label>
                                    <item>Long term programme based on (i), including forces to be
                                        raised and equipped required for victory.</item>
                                    <label>(v)</label>
                                    <item>Set up joint machinery for implementing (ii) (iii) and
                                        (iv).</item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Under the direction of Prime Minister Chiefs of Staff are
                                preparing short general review as a basis for discussion under
                                paragraph 1 (i) above, to be followed by paper on (ii), (iii) and
                                (iv).</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>Chiefs of Staff are giving much thought to machinery for post
                                conference joint collaborations.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>